This paper discusses the challenges of vehicular communication technologies and proposes a method to prioritize transmissions based on the value of information provided by each data source. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper uses analytic hierarchy multicriteria decision processes to determine the value of sensory observations, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also deals with system-level issues related to vehicular networks, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper discusses the security and privacy concerns related to vehicular networks, which is a topic of interest in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category.
